inscription:
underside of storage box lid inscribed: Unsun karuta suzuribako; signed: Yukihiko zo; sealed: Yukihiko;
writing in black ink on both storage box lids and paper cover

Lid verso: ウンスン歌留多硯筥; lid recto: 靫彦蔵  red seal: 新; Label: うんすんかるた蒔絵硯箱　江戸時代　Writing box.  Edo period (1615-1867).  Wood, lacquered, with maki-e (gold lacquer).  Design of un-sun karuta (playing cards).; wrapping paper: ウンスンか (歌)留多  硯箱; another lid verso: ウンスン骨牌硯筥; On the black suzuri: 天下一　　杉本　　豊後
